huntBios.GENERAL_INFORMATION: This unit is largely comprised of USFS land with good and roads and ample hiking trails. Prior scouting of the area and knowledge of bear habitat is critical to hunter success.
huntBios.SAFETY_CONS: This unit is extremely remote with limited cell phone coverage, hunters should plan accordingly. Bear hunting is inherently dangerous and hunters should be cautious while hunting or stalking a bear.
huntBios.WEATHER_CONS: Extreme weather conditions are common on this unit. Hunters should be prepared for all conditions
huntBios.BIOLOGIST_NOTES: Bears can be found throughout the unit, but prior scouting and knowledge of bear behavior are critical to hunter success. Hunters may encounter other recreational users of the area and should be respectful and courteous.

huntBios.GENERAL_INFORMATION: This unit is largely comprised of USFS lands with good roads and ample hiking trails. Scouting and knowledge of bear behavior is critical to hunter success. Hunters may encounter other recreational users and are urged to be courteous and respectful.
huntBios.SAFETY_CONS: The unit is very remote with limited cell phone coverage, please plan accordingly. Bear hunting is inherently dangerous and hunters should be cautious when hunting or stalking a bear.
huntBios.WEATHER_CONS: Extreme weather may be encountered at any time on this hunt. Access to some areas may be limited due to weather conditions.
huntBios.BIOLOGIST_NOTES: Bears can be found throughout the unit, especially in areas of preferred food sources and heavy cover. Please be respectful of other recreational users. Scouting and knowledge of the area is critical to success.

huntBios.GENERAL_INFORMATION: This unit is largely comprised of USFS land with good roads and ample hiking trails in bear habitat. Scouting and knowledge of bear behavior is key to hunter success. Hunters may encounter other recreational users and are encouraged to be courteous and respectful.
huntBios.SAFETY_CONS: Area is very remote with limited cell phone coverage, plan accordingly. Bear hunting is inherently dangerous and hunter should remain cautious while hunting or stalking a bear.
huntBios.WEATHER_CONS: Extreme weather conditions may occur at any time on this unit. Poor weather conditions may limit access or close some areas to hunting.
huntBios.BIOLOGIST_NOTES: Bears can be found throughout the unit, especially in areas of preferred food sources and heavy cover. Shingle Creek, Slate Creek, and Upper-Setting are good locations to begin the scouting process. Please be courteous and respectful to other users that you may encounter while hunting.

huntMaster.SPECIAL_INSTRUCTIONS: Please note: The use of dogs is prohibited on this hunt and there is no early baiting prior to the season opening date.
huntMaster.SPECIAL_PROVISIONS: Before establishing a bait station you must first possess a Certificate of Registration. Please review the rules and procedures for baiting bears in the Black Bear Guidebook
huntMaster.HARVEST_REPORTING: Required: Any harvested bear must be checked by a DWR employee within 48 hours of the date of kill. The DWR employee will affix a permanent possession tag to the pelt or unskinned carcass. You may not possess an unskinned carcass or green pelt after the 48 hour check-in period. If you need to reach a Division employee after regular business hours, over a weekend, or on a holiday, contact your local police dispatch. In addition, you cannot ship a green pelt out of the state of Utah or present it to a taxidermist if the pelt does not have a permanent possession tag attached.

huntBoundaryInfos.BOUNDARY_DESCRIPTION: Summit County--Boundary begins at the Utah-Wyoming state line and SR-150; south on SR-150 to the Summit-Duchesne county line at Hayden Pass; east on this county line to the head of Burnt Fork drainage bottom(Divide Pass/Island Lake); north along this drainage bottom to the Utah-Wyoming state line; west on this state line to SR-150. Excludes all CWMUs. USGS 1:100,000 Maps: Kings Peak. Boundary questions? Call Ogden office, 801-476-2740.
